<emphasis id="E3ED26401B0DFFC1FCA2FDFBFC41FE7B" bold="true" box="[822,977,394,423]" pageId="19" pageNumber="530">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B0DFFC1FB8FFDFBFB0BFE11" authorityName="Contreras" authorityYear="2000" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="530" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="paraguayensis">Ctenomys paraguayensis J. R. Contreras, 2000</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="61F1F00F1B0DFFC1FB55FDC0FB4EFDB0" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798388336" pageId="19" pageNumber="530">“Corate-i, 12 kilometros al oeste de la ciudad de Ayolas, departamento de Misiones, Republica del Paraguay, aproximadamente en las coordenadas: 27°24’S-57°01’'W.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D126FA521B0DFFC1FCACFE07FBD2FCD5" blockId="19.[816,1415,394,817]" pageId="19" pageNumber="530">
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B0DFFC1FCACFE07FBFFFD4F" authorityName="Contreras" authorityYear="2000" box="[824,1135,630,659]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="530" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="paraguayensis">Ctenomys paraguayensis</taxonomicName>
is not classified in any species group. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 52, and form of sperm is unknown. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B0DFFC1FCA0FF61FD0CFC8B" pageId="19" pageNumber="530" type="distribution">
<caption id="85E6AADA1B0DFFC1FCA0FF61FD0CFC8B" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6588284" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6588284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6588284/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="530" targetBox="[206,797,396,810]" targetPageId="19">
<paragraph id="D126FA521B0DFFC1FCA0FF61FD0CFC8B" blockId="19.[816,1415,394,817]" lastBlockId="19.[205,1413,822,1565]" pageId="19" pageNumber="530">
